              "protocolProfileBehavior": {
                "disableBodyPruning": true
              },
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Accept",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/wayfinding/path?api-version=<string>&routesetId=<string>&facilityId=<string>&fromPoint=<string>&fromLevel=<integer>&toPoint=<string>&toLevel=<integer>&avoidFeatures=elevators,elevators&minWidth=0.55",
                  "host": [
                    "{{baseUrl}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "wayfinding",
                    "path"
                  ],
                  "query": [
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) Version number of Azure Maps API.",
                      "key": "api-version",
                      "value": "<string>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) The ID of the routeset to query from.",
                      "key": "routesetId",
                      "value": "<string>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) The identifier of the facility within the routeset where to find the path.",
                      "key": "facilityId",
                      "value": "<string>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) The path origin point in the following format: {latitude},{longitude}.",
                      "key": "fromPoint",
                      "value": "<string>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) The path origin level.",
                      "key": "fromLevel",
                      "value": "<integer>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) The path destination in the following format: {latitude},{longitude}.",
                      "key": "toPoint",
                      "value": "<string>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "(Required) The path destination level.",
                      "key": "toLevel",
                      "value": "<integer>"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "To avoid certain types of connectors in the resulting path. Multiple values can be specified.",
                      "key": "avoidFeatures",
                      "value": "elevators,elevators"
                    },
                    {
                      "description": "The minimum width (in meters) of openings in the searched path. For example, if you specified a minimum width of 0.85, the searched path will avoid openings less than 85 centimeters wide. Note: by using this value, the resulting path points will be buffered from walls and other vertical obstacles by half of the width provided.",
                      "key": "minWidth",
                      "value": "0.55"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                "description": "<br><br> The Wayfinding Service is part of Creator, and adheres to the [Open Geospatial Consortium](http://docs.opengeospatial.org/is/17-069r3/17-069r3.html) standard. Wayfinding uses indoor map data from the [routeset](/rest/api/maps-creator/routeset) to calculate the best path between two locations within the same facility. For more information, see [Wayfinding](/azure/azure-maps/creator-indoor-maps#wayfinding-preview) in the _Creator for indoor maps_ concepts article."
              },
